          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1599495284805-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic </strong>then add to a bowl with your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[6 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[8 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p><p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and tear into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
