            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pizza base mix</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>to the bowl with the yeast</p><p>Gradually add up to 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[110ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>warm water </strong>(you may not need all of it), a little at a time, and gently mix with a plastic spatula until a sticky dough ball has formed</p><p>Tip the <strong>dough ball</strong> out onto a<strong> floured </strong>work surface and cut into<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>dough balls, 1 per person</p><p>Toss each <strong>dough ball</strong> in a light dusting of <strong>flour </strong>until coated, rounding the ball as you go (no need to knead!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1599495307134-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1599495307134-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1599495307134-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1599495307134-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1599495307134-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Press each dough ball<strong> </strong>in the centre and gently push outwards with your fingertips, leaving the rim of the pizza untouched to form a <strong>crust </strong>(don't worry if the dough rips, just stick it back together and carry on!)</p><p>Tip: Dust with extra sprinkles of flour as you go to stop it sticking!</p><p>Keep going until your base is slightly smaller than a side plate (you will make them bigger in the pan!) – these are your <strong>pizza bases</strong></p><p>Heat a large, dry, non-stick, wide-based pan[s] over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599495319166-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599495319166-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599495319166-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599495319166-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1599495319166-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, carefully add the <strong>pizza base[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>to the pan[s], pushing the dough out to the edge to help shape the crust</p><p>Tip: To pick up the pizza dough, gently flip it over the back of your hand to stop it ripping!</p><p>Divide the<strong> tomato sauce </strong>evenly between each pizza and spread it evenly with the back of a spoon (be careful of the hot pan!)</p><p>Cook the pizza base[s] for 3-4 min or until the crust has started to puff up, then remove the heated tray[s] from the oven and slide the pizza base[s]<strong> </strong>onto the tray</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599495325963-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599495325963-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599495325963-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599495325963-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1599495325963-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Repeat this process for the <strong>remaining pizza base[s]</strong></p><p>Tip: Make sure the pizzas don't overlap on the tray to avoid raw dough!</p><p>Top each pizza with the <strong>torn mozzarella</strong> and <strong>wilted spinach</strong>, then crumble over your <strong>goats' cheese</strong> then add dollops of <strong>onion marmalade</strong> and your<strong> basil leaves</strong></p><p>Drizzle the crusts with <strong>olive oil </strong>then put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min or until the cheese has melted and the crust has puffed up and browned</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1599495338101-x200.jpg",
